---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CtaBand from '../components/CtaBand.astro';
import { SITE, orgNode, breadcrumb } from '../data/site';

const personNode = {
  '@type': 'Person',
  '@id': `${SITE.url}/about#britt-midgette`,
  name: 'Britt Midgette',
  jobTitle: 'Founder & Experience Design Director',
  worksFor: { '@id': `${SITE.url}/#organization` },
  url: `${SITE.url}/about`,
  sameAs: [SITE.linkedin],
  knowsAbout: [
    'Digital strategy',
    'UX strategy',
    'Experience design',
    'AI experience design',
    'Enterprise CMS',
    'Design leadership',
  ],
};
const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@graph': [
    {
      '@type': 'AboutPage',
      '@id': `${SITE.url}/about#page`,
      url: `${SITE.url}/about`,
      name: 'About Artifact Digital',
      isPartOf: { '@id': `${SITE.url}/#website` },
      about: { '@id': `${SITE.url}/#organization` },
      mainEntity: { '@id': `${SITE.url}/#organization` },
    },
    orgNode,
    personNode,
    breadcrumb([
      { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
      { name: 'About', path: '/about' },
    ]),
  ],
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About · Artifact Digital"
  description="Artifact Digital is a senior-led digital innovation studio. No handoffs, no juniors learning on your project — the people who set the strategy design and ship it."
  canonical="/about"
  bodyClass="case-page about-page"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <section class="case-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <Breadcrumbs items={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'About' }]} />
      <span class="eyebrow reveal"><span class="eyebrow-dot"></span>About</span>
      <h1 class="case-title">
        <span class="reveal-line"><span>Senior people,</span></span>
        <span class="reveal-line italic"><span>doing the actual work.</span></span>
      </h1>
      <p class="case-lede reveal">
        Artifact is a small, senior-led digital studio by design. We pair strategy,
        design, AI and engineering under one roof, and the people who sell the work
        are the people who do it. No handoffs. No juniors learning on your budget.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section service-intro">
    <div class="container service-prose">
      <p class="reveal">
        Most agencies are built like pyramids. Senior people win the work, then hand
        it down through progressively more junior hands until, somewhere near the
        bottom, the actual thing gets made by whoever was available. The client
        pays for the people at the top and gets the output of the people at the
        bottom. We think that model is quietly broken, and we built Artifact to be
        its opposite.
      </p>
      <p class="reveal">
        We keep the team small on purpose. It means the strategist who understands
        your business is the same person shaping the experience, and often the same
        person in the room when it ships. Nothing gets lost in translation between
        teams, because there are no walls to translate across. You get judgment at
        every step, not just in the pitch.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Leadership philosophy -->
  <section class="section service-section">
    <div class="container service-section__grid">
      <div class="service-section__head">
        <h2 class="service-section__heading reveal-line"><span>How we think about the work</span></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="service-prose service-section__body">
        <p class="reveal">
          A belief that runs through everything we do: leadership isn't about being
          right, it's about being appropriate. Anyone can have opinions. The value
          is in knowing which decision fits this business, this audience, this
          moment — and being willing to take a position and defend it. We bring
          nuance to the table, the kind that comes from years of doing this across
          very different industries and stakes.
        </p>
        <p class="reveal">
          We're also unromantic about tools, including AI. We've been building with
          these tools since the early days, and our view is simple: AI is a force
          multiplier for people who own outcomes, and a crutch for people who don't.
          We use it to move faster and explore wider, and we keep human judgment
          exactly where the consequences live. Technology changes constantly. The
          craft of making good decisions under ambiguity doesn't.
        </p>
        <p class="reveal">
          And we care about craft in the parts most people skip — the empty state,
          the error message, the loading moment, the sentence that could be shorter.
          Those details are where an experience either feels considered or feels
          cheap. Getting them right, over and over, is most of what separates work
          that's fine from work that's memorable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founder -->
  <section class="section service-section" id="britt-midgette">
    <div class="container service-section__grid">
      <div class="service-section__head">
        <span class="section-tag"><span class="tag-dot"></span>Leadership</span>
        <h2 class="service-section__heading reveal-line"><span>Britt Midgette</span></h2>
        <p class="founder-role">Founder &amp; Experience Design Director</p>
        <img
          class="founder-portrait"
          src="/brand_assets/Britt_Midgette.png"
          alt="Britt Midgette, Founder and Experience Design Director of Artifact Digital"
          width="853"
          height="1137"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="service-prose service-section__body">
        <p class="reveal">
          I've spent my career leading digital strategy and experience design for
          organizations across retail, education, healthcare, financial services,
          and global consumer brands — the kind of complex, high-stakes work where
          the details matter and the politics are real. Before tech, I was a pastor
          in a former life, which is a stranger background for a design leader than
          it sounds, and a more useful one: both jobs are ultimately about
          understanding people and helping them make hard decisions together.
        </p>
        <p class="reveal">
          I started Artifact to do the work the way I always believed it should be
          done — senior-led, honest, and close to the craft. I write regularly about
          strategy, design, and AI over in <a href="/insights">Insights</a>, mostly
          to think out loud and start better conversations. If any of it resonates,
          I'd genuinely like to hear from you.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stats -->
  <section class="section stats">
    <div class="container stats-grid">
      <div class="stat reveal">
        <span class="stat__num" data-count="10">0</span><span class="stat__suffix">+</span>
        <p>Years leading digital strategy &amp; design</p>
      </div>
      <div class="stat reveal">
        <span class="stat__num" data-count="40">0</span><span class="stat__suffix">+</span>
        <p>Product, web and digital launches delivered</p>
      </div>
      <div class="stat reveal">
        <span class="stat__num" data-count="100">0</span><span class="stat__suffix">%</span>
        <p>Senior-led on every project — no handoffs</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand heading="Like how we think? Let's talk about your work." />
</BaseLayout>
